rComments: Honestly a genuine guy, extremely captivating during lectures and cares about what he teaches (psychology). The lectures are very interesting and I highly recommend attending them. He assigns relevant and innovative research papers that compliment the material way better than a textbook ever could. I hope he teaches some of my future classes.
Lots of papers to read and materials in the exams are basically from these papers...

Professor Chignell had a rocky start as there was a new textbook in place this year. That man is all heart and not only that he's hilarious. His TA's don't really mark the fairest so try and over explain everything to get the best mark. But as far as he goes he's a really nice man and he's a great lecturer when you really listen hard.

He is a good prof. Always fun to attend his lectures. Knows his stuff. Labs are interesting. The final project (report) is a marks-booster. You are allowed to take notes in the exams. Can not be easier to pass.
Read the book and you will be fine.

He admits that he is a terrible lecturer and expects everyone to just read the text. He gets his slides and assignments from the textbook author.
